<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,721,1108]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,829,855]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Comments:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bocage" authorityYear="1895" box="[351,546,830,855]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Xenopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petersii">
<emphasis box="[351,546,830,855]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Xenopus petersii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widespread in western and central 
<collectingCountry box="[1012,1097,829,855]" name="Angola" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Angola</collectingCountry>
, southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1225,1300,829,855]" name="Gabon" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Gabon</collectingCountry>
to western 
<collectingCountry box="[151,549,865,891]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Democratic Republic of the Congo</collectingCountry>
and northern 
<collectingCountry box="[709,805,865,891]" name="Namibia" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Namibia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Marques, M. P. &amp; Ceriaco, L. M. P. &amp; Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[821,1056,865,891]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="1 - 501" refId="ref38562" refString="Marques, M. P., Ceriaco, L. M. P., Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2018) Diversity and distribution of the amphibians and terrestrial reptiles of Angola atlas of historical and bibliographic records (1840 - 2017). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, Series 4, 65 (Supplement 2), 1 - 501." type="journal article" year="2018">
Marques 
<emphasis box="[929,987,865,891]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). A recent study by 
<bibRefCitation author="Furman, B. L. S. &amp; Bewick, A. J. &amp; Harrison, T. L. &amp; Greenbaum, E. &amp; Gvozdik, V. &amp; Kusamba, C. &amp; Evans, B. J." pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="909 - 925" refId="ref37597" refString="Furman, B. L. S., Bewick, A. J., Harrison, T. L., Greenbaum, E., Gvozdik, V., Kusamba, C. &amp; Evans, B. J. (2015). Pan-African phylogeography of a model organism, the African clawed frog ' Xenopus laevis '. Molecular Ecology, 24 (4), 909 - 925. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / mec. 13076" type="journal article" year="2015">
Furman 
<emphasis box="[1379,1437,865,891]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al.</emphasis>
(2015)
</bibRefCitation>
on the phylogeny of the 
<taxonomicName authority="(Daudin, 1903)" baseAuthorityName="Daudin" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[495,764,901,927]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Xenopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laevis">
<emphasis box="[495,589,901,927]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">X. laevis</emphasis>
(Daudin, 1903)
</taxonomicName>
group recognized 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bocage" authorityYear="1895" box="[968,1081,902,927]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Xenopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petersii">
<emphasis box="[968,1081,902,927]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">X. petersii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid species and supported the revalidation of 
<taxonomicName authority="Hewitt, 1927" authorityName="Hewitt" authorityYear="1927" box="[362,626,937,963]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Xenopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poweri">
<emphasis box="[362,471,938,963]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">X. poweri</emphasis>
Hewitt, 1927
</taxonomicName>
. According to the distribution provided by the authors, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bocage" authorityYear="1895" box="[1242,1357,938,963]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Xenopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petersii">
<emphasis box="[1242,1357,938,963]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">X. petersii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in western and central parts of 
<collectingCountry box="[494,579,973,999]" name="Angola" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Angola</collectingCountry>
, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hewitt" authorityYear="1927" box="[688,797,974,999]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Xenopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poweri">
<emphasis box="[688,797,974,999]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">X. poweri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is limited to eastern and southeastern regions (
<bibRefCitation author="Furman, B. L. S. &amp; Bewick, A. J. &amp; Harrison, T. L. &amp; Greenbaum, E. &amp; Gvozdik, V. &amp; Kusamba, C. &amp; Evans, B. J." pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="909 - 925" refId="ref37597" refString="Furman, B. L. S., Bewick, A. J., Harrison, T. L., Greenbaum, E., Gvozdik, V., Kusamba, C. &amp; Evans, B. J. (2015). Pan-African phylogeography of a model organism, the African clawed frog ' Xenopus laevis '. Molecular Ecology, 24 (4), 909 - 925. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / mec. 13076" type="journal article" year="2015">
Furman 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Conradie, W. &amp; Bill, R. &amp; Branch, W. R." box="[255,484,1009,1036]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="6 - 36" refId="ref36662" refString="Conradie, W., Bill, R. &amp; Branch, W. R. (2016) The herpetofauna of the Cubango, Cuito, and lower Cuando river catchments of south-eastern Angola. Amphibian &amp; Reptile Conservation, 10 (2), [Special Section], e 126, 6 - 36." type="journal article" year="2016">
Conradie 
<emphasis box="[364,412,1009,1035]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Marques, M. P. &amp; Ceriaco, L. M. P. &amp; Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[494,719,1009,1036]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="1 - 501" refId="ref38562" refString="Marques, M. P., Ceriaco, L. M. P., Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2018) Diversity and distribution of the amphibians and terrestrial reptiles of Angola atlas of historical and bibliographic records (1840 - 2017). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, Series 4, 65 (Supplement 2), 1 - 501." type="journal article" year="2018">
Marques 
<emphasis box="[598,653,1009,1035]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). None of the extant specimens has associated localities, but they most likely represent those cited by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ferreira, J. B." box="[564,736,1045,1072]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="159 - 171" refId="ref37198" refString="Ferreira, J. B. (1906) Algumas especies novas ou pouco conhecidas de amphibios e reptis de Angola (Coleccao Newton - 1903 - 1904). Jornal de Sciencias Mathematicas Physicas e Naturaes, Segunda Serie, 7 (26), 159 - 171." type="journal article" year="1906">Ferreira (1906)</bibRefCitation>
from “Cambondo” and “Rio Luinha”, matching the expected geographical range for the species.
</paragraph>
